{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Toggle visibility of empty non-folder tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script toggles the TCP and MCP visibility of tracks matching all of the following criteria:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track has no FX on it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track does not contain any media item\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track has no envelopes\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track is not a folder\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track is not record armed\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A variant of the script is provided which additionally requires tracks to contain the character \u8226? (bullet) in their name. Custom variants can be created by copying the script with the desired track name search string between the apostrophes in the filename.\par}
