{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Track/Item/Take coloring utility - modification of Spacemen Tree's REAchelangelo\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Palette of 24 colors (Color Boxes) + 1 temporary (Temporary - the big color box on top)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Left-click a Color Box to Color Tracks, Items or Takes and set it as Temporary\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Tracks/Items are recognized automatically according to what was lastly clicked while the Takes mode is set manually by the user\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Right-click a Color Box to save the Temporary color into that box\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Load/save different user palettes (.txt files)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Left-click Save button to Save current palette or Right-Click to Save As\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Left-click Load button to load a new palette or Right-Click to load the default palette\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set the Temporary color to the color of the first selected track/item/take according to what was lastly clicked (Get Color button)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Show Hex name of Temporary color\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Left-click Hex name to enter a Hex color code manually (formats: 123456, #123456, # 123456 & 0x123456)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Right-click Hex name to paste it to the clipboard for use with SWS Auto Color/Icons\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Palette is automatically saved to last_palette_on_exit.txt as a backup. If you try to load last_palette_on_exit, then you are prompted to save it with a new name.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Left-click Darker/Brighter buttons to make Temporary Color brighter or darker. Right-click them to make it black/white\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Script saves user palettes in a directory called ReaNoir in the same path as the script. Preferences are saved to ExtState\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Click LD/SV SWS button to load SWSColor files\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Right-Click LD/SV SWS button to save SWSColor files\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Click SWS Colors button to open the SWS Color Management tool\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ability to dock the script to the left or to the right\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Right-click sliders' area to toggle between RGB and HSL mode\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Information displayed on top of ReaNoir when hovering mouse over buttons/sliders\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Ctrl-click on any color box (including the Temporary color box) to color the selected tracks/items/takes from the existing color to the ctrl-clicked color in grades\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Find in the script "MODE OF OPERATION" to set to Normal (RGB/HSL) or Compact (No Sliders) mode\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When in Compact (No Sliders) Mode, Right-click Get Color Button to set Temporary Color Box's color\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Click on "?" on right top corner to display information, Right-Click for manual\sa180\par}
}

